The unified sequence-to-sequence abstraction — where any modality is tokenized and processed by the same Transformer backbone — has also enabled multi-modal models. GPT-4 @achiam2023gpt4 accepts interleaved text and image inputs, while research on unified vision-language architectures continues to expand the range of supported modalities.

// ============================================================================
= Efficient Attention Mechanisms

A fundamental limitation of the standard Transformer is the quadratic complexity of self-attention: for a sequence of length n, computing attention scores requires O(n superscript 2) time and memory. This has motivated an active line of research on efficient attention mechanisms.

FlashAttention @dao2022flashattention addresses this problem at the systems level rather than through algorithmic approximation. By carefully tiling the attention computation to maximize on-chip SRAM usage and minimize reads from high-bandwidth memory (HBM), FlashAttention achieves exact attention with significantly reduced memory footprint and wall-clock time. The technique has been widely adopted in major training frameworks and has enabled training on longer sequences with larger models.

Complementary approaches include sparse attention patterns that restrict each token to attend only to a local window or a set of pre-selected global tokens, linearized attention that approximates the softmax kernel, and state-space models that replace attention entirely with structured recurrent computations. Each approach trades off between computational efficiency and modeling capacity, and the optimal choice depends on sequence length, task requirements, and hardware constraints.

